As shown in the diagram, a [`[$load]`] [`kg`] load is placed on a hydraulic lift. The load is to be raised by pouring oil [`\rho=[$rho_oil]`] [`kg/m^3`] into the 
thin tube connected to the tank. How high does [::h::] need to be to begin
to raise the load?


[@ image( "UBC-FLU-16-011.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

